ALGORITHM :

START: Initialize the program and include necessary header files (iostream, fstream).
MAIN MENU: Display available operations:
1 New Account
2 Deposit Amount
3 Withdraw Amount
4 Balance Enquiry
5 All Account Holder List
6 Close an Account
7 Modify an Account
8 Exit.
USER CHOICE: Input choice via cin.
SWITCH CASE:
Case 1 (New Account): Input name, account number, and initial deposit 
 Write data to binary file (ofstream).
Case 2 (Deposit): Enter account number 
 Search in file 
 Update balance 
 Save back to file.
Case 3 (Withdraw): Enter account number 
 Check if balance > withdrawal amount 
 Update and save.
Case 4 (Balance Enquiry): Enter account number 
 Read from file 
 Display account details.
Case 5 (All List): Loop through file records 
 Display all data.
Case 6 (Close Account): Copy all records except the selected one to a temporary file 
 Replace old file with temporary one.
Case 7 (Modify): Search account 
 Update details (name/type) 
 Rewrite to file.
Case 8 (Exit): Terminate program execution.
REPEAT: Use a do-while loop to return to the Main Menu until "Exit" is chosen.



Key Components & Functions
Account Class: Contains data members like acno, name, deposit, and type.
File Handling: Uses C++ File Streams to manage persistent data in .dat or .txt files.
Validation: Ensures minimum balance requirements (e.g., 
 for Savings, 
 for Current).

